        <enumvalue id="structDali_1_1RenderTask_1_1Property_1a9fe7357a4bb152296d928e044a273cb3afe8870f04f2a802d73b02899573dceac" prot="public">
          <name>REQUIRES_SYNC</name>
          <briefdescription>
<para>name &quot;requiresSync&quot;, type BOOLEAN </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>By default, the sync object is not created. When native image is used as render target, in order to track when the render to pixmap is completed, the GL sync should be enabled. Thus the RENDER_ONCE finished signal can be emit at the correct timing. @SINCE_1_1.29 <simplesect kind="note"><para>The use of GL sync might cause deadlock with multiple access to the single pixmap happening in the same time. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
